# Clerk Authentication Configuration
# Get your keys from https://dashboard.clerk.com

# Clerk Publishable Key (starts with pk_test_ or pk_live_)
VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your_publishable_key_here

# Clerk Secret Key (starts with sk_test_ or sk_live_)
# WARNING: Never commit this to version control or expose it to the client
CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_your_secret_key_here

# Clerk Frontend API (optional, usually auto-configured)
# Example: clerk.your-domain.com
CLERK_FRONTEND_API=

# Clerk JWT Template (optional, for custom JWT claims)
# CLERK_JWT_KEY=

# Webhook Secret (optional, for Clerk webhooks)
# Get this from Clerk Dashboard > Webhooks
# CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_your_webhook_secret

# ==============================================================================
# HOW TO SET UP CLERK AUTHENTICATION
# ==============================================================================
#
# 1. Create a Clerk account at https://clerk.com
#
# 2. Create a new application in your Clerk Dashboard
#
# 3. Go to "API Keys" in the Clerk Dashboard
#
# 4. Copy your Publishable Key and Secret Key
#
# 5. Create a .env.local file in the root of your project
#
# 6. Add your Clerk keys to .env.local:
#    VITE_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_...
#    CLERK_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_...
#
# 7. Configure allowed redirect URLs in Clerk Dashboard:
#    - Development: http://localhost:5173
#    - Production: https://your-domain.com
#
# 8. Set up sign-in and sign-up paths in Clerk Dashboard:
#    - Sign in URL: /sign-in
#    - Sign up URL: /sign-up
#    - After sign in URL: /
#    - After sign up URL: /
#
# 9. (Optional) Enable social providers (Google, GitHub, etc.) in Clerk Dashboard
#
# 10. (Optional) Configure webhooks for user events:
#     - Webhook URL: https://your-domain.com/api/webhooks/clerk
#     - Events: user.created, user.updated, user.deleted
#
# ==============================================================================
# SECURITY NOTES
# ==============================================================================
#
# - NEVER commit .env.local to version control
# - Add .env.local to your .gitignore file
# - Use different keys for development (pk_test_/sk_test_) and production (pk_live_/sk_live_)
# - Rotate your secret keys regularly
# - Only share keys through secure channels (never via email or chat)
#
# ==============================================================================
# ADDITIONAL CLERK FEATURES (Optional)
# ==============================================================================
#
# Multi-factor Authentication (MFA)
# - Enable in Clerk Dashboard > User & Authentication > Multi-factor
#
# Organizations & Teams
# - Enable in Clerk Dashboard > Organizations
#
# Session Configuration
# - Configure session lifetime in Clerk Dashboard > Sessions
#
# Email/SMS Templates
# - Customize in Clerk Dashboard > Emails or SMS
#
# User Metadata
# - Public metadata: Visible to the frontend
# - Private metadata: Only accessible on the backend
# - Unsafe metadata: Can be set by users (use with caution)
#
# ==============================================================================
